  "stem": "<p>Triangle <math><mi>F</mi><mi>G</mi><mi>H</mi></math> is similar to triangle <math><mi>J</mi><mi>K</mi><mi>L</mi></math>, where angle <math><mi>F</mi></math> corresponds to angle <math><mi>J</mi></math> and angles <math><mi>G</mi></math> and <math><mi>K</mi></math> are right angles. If <math><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>24</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac></math>, what is the value of <math><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>J</mi><mo>)</mo></math>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p><math><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p><math><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>24</mn></mfrac></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p><math><mfrac><mn>25</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "d",
      "content": "<p><math><mfrac><mn>24</mn><mn>25</mn></mfrac></math></p>"
    }
  ],
  "keys": [
    "d"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. Corresponding angles in similar triangles are congruent, so the measure of angle J equals the measure of angle F. Therefore sin(J) = sin(F) = 24/25.</p><p>Choice A gives cos(F) (using the 7-24-25 triple). Choice B is 1/sin(F). Choice C is 1/cos(F).</p>",
